   51: ### RESULTS — anchored scenarios (`npm run e4:scenarios`, N=1500,K=150, 800 worlds)
   52: > **CORRECTION:** `PRO_CENTRAL` is the central's declared full-favourable endpoint, and the central wins there.
   53: > `NO_MYOPIA` is the separate harm-aware and otherwise-competent continuity bundle at +6.1%, **not a myopia
   54: > isolation**; `MYOPIA_OFF` is the two-harm-coordinate diagnostic contrast at +30.4%. Authoritative configs live in
   55: > `scenario-configs.mjs`; the regression pins executable outcome ORDERING only, not exact configs, magnitudes,
   56: > labels, or prose.
   57: 
   58: | scenario | m (gap) | 95% CI | Core v0 delivers | central delivers | winner |
   59: |---|---|---|---|---|---|
   60: | PRO-CENTRAL (central's declared full-favourable endpoint) | **−29.5%** | [−29.9, −29.1] | 68% of oracle | 98% | **central** |
   61: | NO-MYOPIA (harm-aware and otherwise-competent continuity bundle) | **+6.1%** | [5.8, 6.4] | 91% | 85% | ≈ parity |
   62: | PROBABLE (source-motivated reference) | **+46.6%** | [46.0, 47.4] | 91% | 45% | Core v0 |
   63: | PRO-DISTRIBUTED (favourable, moderate) | **+199.8%** | [197, 202] | 96% | −104% (destroys value) | Core v0 |
   64: 
   65: - **Level field (both ways):** the central has a genuine winning region — under its declared full-favourable endpoint (low
   66:   participation + competent, harm-aware central) it wins ~30% and delivers 98% of the oracle. Core v0 wins under the
   67:   probable reference. The story from D/O: Core v0 is fairly robust (68–96%); the central swings 45%→85%→98% (or −104%
   68:   when myopic + harmful) — it depends on whether it sees the anti-value AND on citizen participation.
   69: - **Continuity / reconciliation with the NO-GO:** in this sequential, path-dependent decomposition, `MYOPIA_OFF`
   70:   changes only `s_exp,b_H_C` and reduces the gap `+46.6% → +30.4%`, or 16.2 of the 40.5-point decline to `NO_MYOPIA`
   71:   (~40%). The further move to the harm-aware and otherwise-competent `NO_MYOPIA` bundle reduces it by 24.3 points
   72:   (~60%). `NO_MYOPIA` is the continuity anchor to the symmetry-gate near-parity regime; this is a qualitative
   73:   reconciliation hypothesis across different DGPs, not a reproduced limit.
   74: 
   75: ### RESULTS — ceteris-paribus frontiers (`npm run e4:frontier`)
   76: - **Robustness over five plotted slices (NOT all parameters):** across the five prespecified one-factor slices
   77:   (`s_exp, b_H_C, p, beta, a_V`), none crosses the parity frontier from the PROBABLE scenario within its plotted
   78:   range — Core v0 wins throughout (+25% to +54%). This is a limited robustness statement over those five slices;
   79:   reaching parity requires COMBINING central-favourable conditions (and other coordinates can flip the sign — e.g.
   80:   the targeted PRO_CENTRAL-region probe in `e4:evidence`).
   81: - **Combined scenario-path frontier (CORRECTED, Codex v7):** interpolating PROBABLE → the declared central-favourable
   82:   endpoint (`PRO_CENTRAL`), m falls +47% → −30%; the **frontier (m=0) is at t ≈ 0.57** — i.e. conditions ~57%
   83:   of the way from probable toward the declared central-favourable endpoint flip the winner to the central, within the
   84:   declared interpolation segment (the earlier "t≈1.13 / beyond realistic" claim was wrong — it used a partial 8-knob
   85:   path). Honest headline: *which side a real setting falls on depends on where a measured target configuration would
   86:   lie between the declared scenarios; none of the five plotted slices decides it alone.* `t` is an illustrative
   87:   linear mix, not a calibrated competence scale.
