    Integrate E4 v1.14 four-scenario robustness map into paper.md + paper.es.md (EN/ES mirror)
    
    Adds a 'realistic-myopia extension (v1.14)' subsection right after the symmetry-gate methods
    block (the gate becomes the NO_MYOPIA harm-aware anchor): the salience-gated harm model, four
    declared scenarios + one diagnostic contrast (central WINS its declared full-favourable endpoint
    ~98% vs ~68%; probable ~91% vs ~45%; distributed-favourable central delivers negative value),
    the honest 40/60 attribution, and the explicit reconciliation with the pre-registered Δ~0.025 NO-GO
    (same phenomenon under opposite assumptions). Abstract updated in both languages. Magnitudes labeled
    source-motivated declared reference/stress points, not calibrated impact; no multiplier/ratio
    notation introduced. Section parity 17/17; check-anchors clean.
    
    Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>

