+# Codex critique — E4 v1.14 integration into the paper
+
+## Verdict
+
+**YES — the E4 integration in `drafts/paper.md` and `drafts/paper.es.md` is publication-ready as a comparative-institutions robustness result under the stated bar.**
+
+This verdict is limited to the new E4 abstract sentences and realistic-myopia subsections. It does not re-review the already blessed E4 code or impose a calibrated-impact standard.
+
+## Checks
+
+- **Faithfulness: VERIFIED.** The integrated subsections report the central's declared full-favourable endpoint as a central win at approximately 98% versus 68%, the probable reference as approximately 91% versus 45% for distributed and central, and the distributed-favourable case as positive distributed delivery against negative central value (`drafts/paper.md:631-637`; `drafts/paper.es.md:691-697`). `npm run e4:scenarios` reproduced the underlying 97.6%/68.1%, 91.2%/44.6%, and -104.0%/95.8% values. The prose also preserves the path-dependent sequential attribution: harm-myopia alone accounts for about 40% of the move, with the further competent no-myopia bundle accounting for the remaining approximately 60% (`drafts/paper.md:637-640`; `drafts/paper.es.md:697-701`). It places parity partway along the declared probable-to-central-favourable segment and labels the magnitudes as source-motivated declared reference and stress points, not calibrated bands (`drafts/paper.md:645-653`; `drafts/paper.es.md:705-714`).
+
+- **NO-GO reconciliation: VERIFIED.** Both versions identify the pre-registered delta of approximately 0.025 with the competent, harm-aware near-parity regime and explicitly describe E4 and the symmetry gate as the same phenomenon under opposite assumptions, not a contradiction (`drafts/paper.md:639-644`; `drafts/paper.es.md:699-705`). The abstract additions preserve the same reconciliation and calibrated-impact disclaimer (`drafts/paper.md:13`; `drafts/paper.es.md:15`). This is comparative-assumption mapping, not result-shopping.
+
+- **No overclaim, dishonest label, or multiplier notation: VERIFIED.** The additions use the declared scenario labels, expose harm-myopia as the load-bearing and least empirically pinned assumption, and exclude administrative-cost and leakage channels. They introduce no multiplier-form `x`, `×`, or `D/C` notation and make no claim about a “best plausible” case, “where reality sits,” or calibrated impact.
+
+- **EN↔ES parity: VERIFIED.** The English and Spanish additions match in scenario count, direction, magnitudes, sequential attribution, reconciliation, frontier location, and caveats. The Spanish wording “a mitad del segmento declarado” remains consistent with the blessed frontier at `t approximately 0.57`; it does not create a different substantive or calibrated claim.
+
+## Remaining blockers
+
+**None.**

